10/01/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU wants to see the constitutional charter of the new joint state of Serbia and Montenegro adopted by 15 January, according to Christina Gallach, a representative of EU foreign policy chief Javier Solana. The text of the law on enacting the charter will likely be finalised at Friday's (10 January) session of the constitutional commission. The Montenegrin and Serbian sides have both expressed readiness to overcome their differences and seal the document. (B92, Tanjug, FoNet, BBC - 09/01/02)
